id="post-2772" class="post-2772 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-environment tag-brown-field tag-clean tag-green tag-plants tag-pollution tag-sustainable"><h2 class="entry-title"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2011/03/03/plants-eat-pollution/" title="Permalink to Plants Eat Pollution" rel="bookmark">Plants Eat Pollution</a></h2><div
class="entry-meta"> <span
class="entry-date" title="2011/03/03 11:40 am"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2011/03/03/plants-eat-pollution/" title="Plants Eat Pollution" rel="bookmark">2011/03/03 11:40 am</a></span><span
class="entry-meta-sep"> / </span><span
class="entry-author author vcard"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/author/administrator/" title="by Adam Clare" rel="author">Adam Clare</a></span></div><div
class="entry-content clearfix"><p>We all know that plants are really good at cleaning the air and that&#8217;s absolutely a good thing. Nowadays more and more research is looking at using plants to clean more than just the air. Recently, a researcher in Ontario has used plants to clean up pollutants in a brown field site.</p><blockquote><p>“Traditionally, we dig up the contamination and take it to a hazardous-waste dumpsite or incineration facility, but then the soil is lost,” she says. “But, in using phytoextraction &#8230; after we pull all the contaminants out, you’ve still got this natural resource of the soil itself.”</p><p>The composted material may still need to be disposed of as hazardous waste, but the volume of contaminated matter has been greatly reduced, says Dr. Zeeb.</p></blockquote><p><a
href="http://www.universityaffairs.ca/pollutant-eating-plants-save-the-soil.aspx">Read the rest here.</a></p><p>Thanks Mike!</p><div
class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-1111807-2772-538344bb8e49c' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/#blog_id=1111807&amp;post_id=2772&amp;origin=www.thingsaregood.com&amp;obj_id=1111807-2772-538344bb8e49c' data-name='like-post-frame-1111807-2772-538344bb8e49c'><h3 class='sd-title'>Like this:</h3><div
